ophetic legacy and as patrons of fellow believers, and their association with the glorious history of ancient Syrian cities and the expanding sacred landscape. Based upon a variety of literary sources, including hitherto unexplored saintly vitas, the investigation aims to contribute to an understanding of the process through which the religious and charismatic leadership of the venerated shaykhs was sustained and diffused, and their holiness emplaced and commemorated.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aSufismzSyriaxHistoryyTo 1500. 4aHistory. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh  aCharismatic religious teaching.  aMedieval Sufi Masters.  aMedieval Syria.  aMysticism.  aShaykh.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z9783110753851oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781641892094zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781641892094zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781641892094.jpg  a978-3-11-074322-7 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7 DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  a97